.\" termin.al-name: now
.\" termin.al-usage: now
.\" termin.al-summary: Open now content.
.TH NOW 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
now \- Open now content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
now
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens the fixed virtual document
.B ~/now.md
as rendered Markdown in the current pane's inline viewer. In the deterministic demo this is published snapshot content, not a live activity feed.
.SH VIEWER
Use j/k or arrows, PageUp/b and PageDown/Space, g/G, / search, n/N, and q or Escape to return. Mobile controls expose Escape, movement and Prefix.
.SH FAILURES
Extra arguments are rejected. Missing content produces the stable content-unavailable diagnostic; cancellation opens nothing.
.SH NOTES
Returning preserves the shell transcript, history and working directory. The document is read-only and is not refreshed by the command.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ now
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
changelog(1), about(1), stats(1)
